        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Objective-C'); ?>
        <p><strong>Objective-C</strong> is a general-purpose, object-oriented programming language that adds <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Smalltalk', 'L'); ?>-style messaging to the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('C', 'L'); ?> programming language.</p>
        <p>It is the main programming language used by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Apple', 'C'); ?> for the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('OS X', 'OS'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('iOS', 'OS'); ?> operating systems, and their respective application programming interfaces (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('API', 'SD'); ?>s), <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Cocoa', 'SD'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Cocoa Touch', 'SD'); ?>.</p>
        <p>The programming language Objective-C was originally developed in the early 1980s.</p>
        <p>It was selected as the main language used by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('NeXT', 'C'); ?> for its <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('NeXTSTEP', 'OS'); ?> operating system, from which OS X and iOS are derived.</p>
